      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">31.110</ph> Indirect cost rate certification
and penalties on unallowable costs.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d1917e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1931e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                   Certain contracts require certification
of the indirect cost rates proposed for final payment purposes.
See <xref href="FAR-i1075098.dita#i1075098"
                        base="i1075098"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">42.703-2</xref> for administrative
procedures regarding the certification provisions and the related
contract clause prescription.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d1931e29" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                   If unallowable
costs are included in final indirect cost settlement proposals,
penalties may be assessed. See 42.709 for administrative procedures
regarding the penalty assessment provisions and the related contract
clause prescription.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
